(fifthQuint)Efficacy and Safety of a PIKA Rabies Vaccine Containing the PIKA Adjuvant With an Accelerated Regimen.

 A multi-center, open labelled, randomized study in healthy naive adult subjects.

 Subjects were randomly assigned to groups A (60) and B (60).

 Group A as a control arm of the study, had received a commercially available rabies vaccine, RABIPUR(R).

 Group B had received doses of the investigational PIKA rabies vaccine in an accelerated regimen.

 Group A followed the vaccine regimen of (1-1-1-1),one injection on days 0, 3, 7 and 14 was administered respectively.

 Group B received the accelerated regimen (2-2-1), two injections on both days 0 and 3 were administered in different arms; and only one injection was administered on day 7.

